    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-23T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (<persName corresp="#p_I2"
                        >Italy</persName>)/6–2345: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 568<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in <persName corresp="#p_Y1">Yugoslavia</persName>
                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SH2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-23T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 23, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>197. Referring to <persName corresp="#p_TMJB1">Tito</persName>’s published remark
                    that problem of civil govt of Venezia Giulia is still open (<gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 109 [<hi rend="italic">188</hi>], June
                        22<note n="1" xml:id="d568fn1">
                        <ref target="#d567">Document No. 567</ref>.</note>) I suggest that US and
                        <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> govts instruct Belgrade Embassies to
                    remind Yugo Govt that question was settled by Article 3 of Belgrade Agreements
                    and that attempts to stir up trouble in area under <gloss target="#t_AMG1"
                        >AMG</gloss> is unlikely to benefit Yugos position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SH2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shantz</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
